"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533052\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533052\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 19, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vjz1665702778665.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vjz1665702778665.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vjz1665702778665.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vjz1665702778665\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To integrate custom functionality into the Uniface IDE, you can use the Worksheet\n      Plug-In API to create forms that can be added as worksheets to IDE editors. You must then add\n      the components to the Uniface IDE resources and configure the IDE to use them.</p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1775e1_d1776e1_d1777e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a Form component that provides the functionality you want to add to an IDE editor. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxt1665702612061.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxt1665702612061.html\" title=\"Forms are presentation components used in desktop applications and reports are used for printing. They are created in the same way.\">Constructing Forms and Reports</a>.\n                  </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1778e1_d1779e1_d1780e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the Form's <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Type</span> property to <code class=\"ph codeph\">contained</code>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1781e1_d1782e1_d1783e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__p_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1\">Implement the following mandatory operations plug-in\n               operations:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1784e1_d1785e1_d1786e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hgs1665702775284.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hgs1665702775284.html\" title=\"Return the version number of the IDE Worksheet Plug-In API that is used by this component.\">getVersion</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1787e1_d1788e1_d1789e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xsx1665702775354.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xsx1665702775354.html\" title=\"Return a Struct with the worksheet title and tooltip.\">getWorksheetOptions</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jod1665702775423.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jod1665702775423.html\" title=\"Activate the worksheet plug-in form for the current main development object.\">ws_activate</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wve1665702775211.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wve1665702775211.html\" title=\"A user-defined worksheet is a contained form component that implements worksheet operations, which can be called by the Uniface IDE. These operations ensure that the worksheet can respond appropriately to IDE events.\">Worksheet Plug-In Operations</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1793e1_d1794e1_d1795e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__p_d4391e1_d4392e1_d4393e1\">Optionally, implement the following operations,\n               which enable the component to respond to IDE events:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1796e1_d1797e1_d1798e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kns1665702775492.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kns1665702775492.html\" title=\"Defines the behavior of the worksheet plug-in component when the worksheet is selected and becomes visible.\">ws_getsVisible</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1799e1_d1800e1_d1801e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hpl1665702775565.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hpl1665702775565.html\" title=\"Defines the behavior of the worksheet plug-in component when another worksheet is selected and the current worksheet becomes invisible.\">ws_getsInvisible</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1802e1_d1803e1_d1804e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ihl1665702775639.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ihl1665702775639.html\" title=\"Defines the behavior of the worksheet plug-in component when the main development object being edited is renamed.\">ws_objectRenamed</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1805e1_d1806e1_d1807e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xnq1665702775708.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xnq1665702775708.html\" title=\"Defines the behavior of the worksheet plug-in component when the IDE issues a request to refresh the current main object editor.\">ws_refresh</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wve1665702775211.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wve1665702775211.html\" title=\"A user-defined worksheet is a contained form component that implements worksheet operations, which can be called by the Uniface IDE. These operations ensure that the worksheet can respond appropriately to IDE events.\">Worksheet Plug-In Operations</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1808e1_d1809e1_d1810e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If the worksheet is used to modify objects, call IDE API operations to request the\n               IDE to refresh objects and/or editors. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"inj1665702764312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/inj1665702764312.html\" title=\"The component API IDE_API_1 provides an interface to selected IDE functionality, enabling menu and worksheet plug-ins to refresh editors or send messages to the Messages Output tab.\">IDE API Operations</a>.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1811e1_d1812e1_d1813e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, package your custom components into a Uniface archive file.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1814e1_d1815e1_d1816e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Uniface IDE assignment file, specify the location of the components in the\n               [RESOURCES] section. You can specify a UAR, or the <span class=\"ph filepath\">resources</span>\n               directory where the compiled components are located. For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104vjz1665702778665_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__codeblock_h4h_tvl_mzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[RESOURCES]\n; D:/unifaceData/project/resources ; dir where IDE puts compiled components\nD:/uniface10/project/USERWORKSHEETS.UAR \nusys:ide.uar\nusys:ide_messages.uar</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__li_d1817e1_d1818e1_d1819e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__p_d4394e1_d4395e1_d4396e1\">In the [LOGICALS] section of the Uniface IDE\n               assignment file, define worksheet logicals to specify the editor and its custom\n               worksheets. For example:</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104vjz1665702778665_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__codeblock_ayf_3wl_mzb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[LOGICALS]\n;worksheet logicals\nIDE_DEFINE_WORKSHEETS_PRJ=MY_VIEW, MY_EXPORT\nIDE_DEFINE_WORKSHEETS_CPT=MY_VIEW \n...</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">If you have modified a worksheet’s logical definition, the IDE detects this and\n                  restarts the editor involved.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__p_d4397e1_d4398e1_d4399e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uxq1665702763473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uxq1665702763473.html\" title=\"To add user-defined worksheets and menus to the IDE you must define the appropriate logicals in the ide.asn file.\">Logicals for IDE Menu and Worksheet Plug-Ins</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vjz1665702778665__note_mt2_nwl_mzb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The IDE does not detect changes made to the title and\n                  tooltip (in the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getWorksheetOptions</span> operation). If you change\n                  these, you need to restart your Editor for the changes to take effect.</div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rty1665702763402.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>IDE Worksheet Plug-Ins</a><p>Worksheet plug-ins are contained forms that can be added as user-defined worksheets to editors for main development objects, such as the entity editor and the component editor. It is possible to define multiple worksheets for each type of editor.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533052\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533052\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Add User-Defined Worksheets to IDE Editors Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 19, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 To integrate custom functionality into the Uniface IDE, you can use the Worksheet Plug-In API to create forms that can be added as worksheets to IDE editors. You must then add the components to the Uniface IDE resources and configure the IDE to use them. Create a Form component that provides the functionality you want to add to an IDE editor. For more information, see Constructing Forms and Reports . Set the Form's Window Type property to contained . Implement the following mandatory operations plug-in operations: getVersion getWorksheetOptions ws_activate For more information, see Worksheet Plug-In Operations . Optionally, implement the following operations, which enable the component to respond to IDE events: ws_getsVisible ws_getsInvisible ws_objectRenamed ws_refresh For more information, see Worksheet Plug-In Operations . If the worksheet is used to modify objects, call IDE API operations to request the IDE to refresh objects and/or editors. For more information, see IDE API Operations . Optionally, package your custom components into a Uniface archive file. In the Uniface IDE assignment file, specify the location of the components in the [RESOURCES] section. You can specify a UAR, or the resources directory where the compiled components are located. For example: Explain this code [RESOURCES] ; D:/unifaceData/project/resources ; dir where IDE puts compiled components D:/uniface10/project/USERWORKSHEETS.UAR usys:ide.uar usys:ide_messages.uar Copy In the [LOGICALS] section of the Uniface IDE assignment file, define worksheet logicals to specify the editor and its custom worksheets. For example: Explain this code [LOGICALS] ;worksheet logicals IDE_DEFINE_WORKSHEETS_PRJ=MY_VIEW, MY_EXPORT IDE_DEFINE_WORKSHEETS_CPT=MY_VIEW ... Copy If you have modified a worksheet’s logical definition, the IDE detects this and restarts the editor involved. For more information, see Logicals for IDE Menu and Worksheet Plug-Ins . Note: The IDE does not detect changes made to the title and tooltip (in the getWorksheetOptions operation). If you change these, you need to restart your Editor for the changes to take effect. Related Links IDE Worksheet Plug-Ins Worksheet plug-ins are contained forms that can be added as user-defined worksheets to editors for main development objects, such as the entity editor and the component editor. It is possible to define multiple worksheets for each type of editor. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}